frus:attachment.p:
Between 1919–1925, 577.800 people migrated from Poland;
                                        between 1926–1930, 964.000; between 1931–1935, 229.000; in
                                        the succeeding years the number of emigrants was oscillating
                                        between 50 and 100 thousand a year (1937—102.400;
                                        1938—129.100).
